details:
Case 146 is a 64 year-old female Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. She is a contact of Case 134, and is linked to the cluster involving the private dinner function at SAFRA Jurong.

She reported onset of symptoms on 4 March, and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 5 March. She presented at National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) on 7 March, and subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 8 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, she mostly stayed at her home in the Yio Chu Kang Road area.

She has recovered from the infection and have been discharged from hospital today (14 March).
